# Yarn 1.x reads --save-exact from here (NOT from .npmrc). Keeps local
# `yarn add` pinning to exact versions, matching the exact-pin policy in
# SUPPLY-CHAIN-SECURITY.md §1 and the manual lockfile review.
--save-exact true

# NOTE: `ignore-scripts` is deliberately NOT set (supply-chain plan, Option A).
# This repo depends on native packages whose postinstall builds a platform
# binary (sharp via next/image; pdfjs-dist for the terms/privacy PDF viewer).
# Globally ignoring scripts would break image optimization / PDF rendering with
# no in-repo rebuild path. Postinstall-abuse (threat #3) is instead defended by
# the install-hook review gate (.supply-chain/install-hooks.allowlist) + the
# 7-day cooldown + frozen lockfile. Do NOT add `ignore-scripts true` without
# first adding a documented native-dep rebuild path. See SUPPLY-CHAIN-SECURITY.md §6.
